Significant road closures and parking restrictions will be in effect across the city and Pyrmont on New Year's Eve. In the Sydney CBD, some roads close from as early as 4am, roads in Circular Quay and The Rocks close by 2pm, followed by major closures in the city centre and Pyrmont from 7pm. Roads start reopening from 1.30am NYD.

The Cahill Expressway southbound lanes 7 + 8 on the Harbour Bridge and Circular Quay Overpass will close from 6am on NYE.

Ahead of the fireworks, the Sydney Harbour Bridge will be completely closed from 11pm. The Anzac Bridge citybound lanes will close from 8.30pm to 9.30pm and from 11pm to 1.30am, Rozelle Interchange tunnel and exits to Anzac Bridge will also close during these times.

  • 4am – 6am: Macquarie St from Bridge St to the Sydney Opera House.
  • 5am – 4am: Art Gallery Rd and Mrs Macquaries Rd in the Royal Botanic Garden & Domain.
  • 6am – 10am (1 Jan): Circular Quay West and George St between Lower Fort St and Hickson Rd
  • 6am – 4am: Cahill Expressway lanes 7 + 8 on the Harbour Bridge and overpass at Circular Quay. Use the Harbour Bridge or Tunnel instead for travel to/from the east. Cahill Walkway will close at 6am.
  • 10am – 4am: Macquarie St between Bridge St and Shakespeare Pl, Bridge St at Macquarie St and Phillip Ln
  • 12pm – 4am: Hickson Rd between Towns Place, Millers Point and Watermans Quay, Barangaroo, and Barton St.

  • 6pm – 4am: Darling Island Rd at Pyrmont. The Sydney Harbour Bridge walkway and cycleway will close from 6pm-2am.
  • 7pm – 4am: Major roads in the CBD centre from Wynyard to Hyde Park including Macquarie St, Elizabeth St, Castlereagh St, Pitt St, King St, Bent St, Hunter St, Market St, Park St, Druitt St, as well as sections of Hickson Rd, Towns Place, Dalgety Rd, Wheat Rd at King St Wharf and Pirrama Rd in Pyrmont.
